      {
        "step": 6,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Your **⭐ Starfish LED circuit** is ready! Here's a full breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 🌟 Starfish Shape — Layout Explained\n\nThe 6 orange LEDs are arranged to represent a **5-armed starfish**:\n\n```\n        💡 Arm 1\n        |\n💡Arm5 — 💡Center — 💡Arm2\n        |\n        💡 Arm 3\n        |\n        💡 Arm 4\n```\n\n| LED | Role |\n|-----|------|\n| `LED_Center` | 🟠 Body / core of the starfish |\n| `LED_Arm1` | 🟠 Top arm |\n| `LED_Arm2` | 🟠 Upper-right arm |\n| `LED_Arm3` | 🟠 Lower-right arm |\n| `LED_Arm4` | 🟠 Lower-left arm |\n| `LED_Arm5` | 🟠 Upper-left arm |\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ How It Works\n\n- **All 6 LEDs** are wired in parallel to **Arduino pin D13**\n- Each LED has its own **220Ω resistor** for current protection\n- The sketch blinks all of them **simultaneously** — ON for 600ms, OFF for 400ms\n\n---\n\n## 📟 Sketch Summary\n\n```cpp\nconst int LED_PIN = 13;\n\nvoid setup() {\n  pinMode(LED_PIN, OUTPUT);\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  digitalWrite(LED_PIN, HIGH); // ✨ All ON\n  delay(600);\n  digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW);  // 🌑 All OFF\n  delay(400);\n}\n```\n\n> 💡 **Tip:** Want a fancier effect? I can add a **breathing glow** (PWM fade), **wave pattern** across the arms, or even different **colors per arm** using RGB LEDs!"
